HEADWORD: Plush
<hw>Plush</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>pluche</ets>,
<ets>peluche</ets> (cf. It. <ets>peluzzo</ets>), fr. L. <ets>pilus</ets>
hair. See <er>pile</er> hair, and cf. <er>Peruke</er>.]</ety> <def>A
textile fabric with a nap or shag on one side, longer and softer than
the nap of velvet.</def> <rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

